title: Avocado & Cherry Tomato Ramen Noodle Bowl with Lemon Basil Vinaigrette
summary: The recipe Avocado & Cherry Tomato Ramen Noodle Bowl with Lemon Basil Vinaigrette could satisfy your Japanese craving in around 20 minutes. This dairy free recipe serves 2 and costs $3.74 per serving. One serving contains 860 calories, 18g of protein, and 42g of fat. 1 person has made this recipe and would make it again. A mixture of avocado, lemon zest, lemon basil, and a handful of other ingredients are all it takes to make this recipe so tasty. To use up the honey you could follow this main course with the Honey Gingerbread as a dessert. Not a lot of people really liked this main course. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 77%. This score is good. Similar recipes include Tomato, Avocado, Corn and Basil Salad With Lemon-Balsamic Vinaigrette, Ramen Noodle Bowl, and Easy Ramen Noodle Bowl.

winePairing.pairingText: Riesling, Sake, and Sauvignon Blanc are great choices for Ramen Noodles. Saké is an obvious choice when it comes to Japanese food. If you want to stick to grape wine, though, you might opt for sauvignon blanc or riesling. The J.J. Prum Graacher Himmelreich Kabinett Riesling with a 4.4 out of 5 star rating seems like a good match. It costs about 22 dollars per bottle.

productMatches.title: J.J. Prum Graacher Himmelreich Kabinett Riesling
productMatches.description:
Despite its still youthful freshness it shows the fine fruity Riesling characteristic and an underlying hint of mineral from the blue/grey Devonian slate soil.

Serve this refreshing wine slightly chilled! As aperitif and, especially when more matured, in combination with seafood or poultry.

instructions: Add all ingredients to a small mixing bowl and whisk well. Set aside for at least a half hour, if possible, to let the flavors meld. Taste, and add more salt if needed, one pinch at a time.Bring a medium pot of water to boil. Add the ramen noodles and reduce heat slightly to maintain an active simmer without boiling over. Cook for three minutes (or according to package directions). Drain in a colander and set aside to cool to room temperature (this takes just a few minutes).When the ramen noodles have cooled, toss them with one tablespoon of olive oil plus two tablespoons of the vinaigrette. Divide the noodles evenly between two entree-sized bowls. Top each bowl with half of the sliced tomatoes and avocados, and drizzle the remaining vinaigrette evenly over each. Garnish with minced basil.
